      • retrieveTogetherTime

        public int retrieveTogetherTime(Timeline other,
                                java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Integer> locationAndTimeSpent)
        Takes in another timeline and a HashMap of locations and time spent together in each place and calculates the amount of time for which this timeline and the other timeline overlap (i.e. spend time together) and puts the overlap time (and place) in the input HashMap. Keeps track of the places where the timelines overlap.
        Parameters:
        other - Timeline to be checked against.
        locationAndTimeSpent - HashMap of places and time spent in each location.
        Returns:
        overlap/together time, in seconds.

      • retrieveTogetherTime

        public int retrieveTogetherTime(Timeline other)
        Takes in another timeline and calculates the amount of time for which this timeline and the other timeline overlap (i.e. spend time together). Does not keep track of the places where the timelines overlap.
        Parameters:
        other - Timeline to be checked against.
        Returns:
        overlap/together time, in seconds.

      • merge

        public Timeline merge(Timeline other)
        Takes in another timeline and merges it with this timeline. Merging happens when there is overlap in the timelines (i.e. there are LocationIntervals that have the same location and have time interval overlaps).
        Parameters:
        other - Timeline to be checked against.
        Returns:
        merged Timeline of the two input timelines.

      • calculateTimeSpent

        public void calculateTimeSpent(java.util.TreeMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Integer> togetherTime)
        Calculates the time spent in each location on the timeline and maps it into the input map. If the map already contains the place, add to the time spent to the existing time. If not, create new key-value pair.
        Parameters:
        togetherTime - HashMap of places and time spent together in each location.
